oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Daguerreotype of Brig. Gen. Edward P. Fyffe
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Daguerreotype of Brig. Gen. Edward P. Fyffe. Fyffe, a physician, enlisted as a Colonel, 26th Ohio Vol. Inf. Regt. on June 10, 1861, promoted to Brevet Brigadier Gen. on March 13, 1865. He was at Stones River. He was from Urbana (Champaign County), Ohio. He attended West Point.
